<task id="119" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Acceptance test "summarize this NDA" → Summarize-NDA top-1; Phase 5 exit gate</title>
    <phase>5: WP2 File-Aware Classification</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>117,118</dependencies>
    <blocks>120</blocks>
    <tags>testing, e2e-test, verification, architecture-binding</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'testing' + 'e2e-test' + 'verification'; exit-gate verification; STANDARD per task-execute Step 0.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>5-E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author the binding acceptance test for Phase 5 — "summarize this NDA" + NDA upload routes to Summarize-NDA playbook as top-1 candidate. Also produce the Phase 5 exit-gate report verifying FR-15 through FR-21 are satisfied. Note: PB-009 (Summarize-NDA) is authored in Phase 6 (tasks 126/130) — for Phase 5 exit, the acceptance test asserts that the dispatcher would route correctly when the playbook is present (use a stub playbook if PB-009 is not yet authored).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform program lead + test engineer. Verification + exit-gate role.</role>

  <goal>
    Acceptance test passes: "summarize this NDA" + NDA PDF → dispatcher returns `summarize-nda` (or `summarize-document-chat` if `summarize-nda` playbook not yet indexed) as top-1 with confidence ≥0.7. Phase 5 exit-gate report at `notes/handoffs/119-phase5-exit-gate.md` confirms FR-15-21 + supporting telemetry/load-test artifacts. Gate transitions to Phase 6.
  </prompt>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec Success Criteria T-006 + FR-43. The NDA acceptance test is the binding signal that file-aware classification works end-to-end. Caveat: `summarize-nda` playbook isn't authored until Phase 6 tasks 126/130. For Phase 5 exit, the test can assert: (a) when a playbook indexed with `documentTypes: ["nda"]` is present, the dispatcher routes to it top-1 for "summarize this NDA" + NDA upload; (b) all FR-15 through FR-21 acceptance criteria from spec.md hold. The full Phase 6 binding test (132) re-runs this with the real PB-009.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Phase5/</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15-21">All Phase 5 functional requirements satisfied per acceptance criteria.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec T-006">"Summarize this NDA" + NDA upload routes to NDA-specific playbook top-1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Test fixtures use synthetic NDA — no real client data.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If acceptance test or FR fails verification, escalate per CLAUDE.md §6.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/design.md</file>
