      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Locate or seed a stub playbook indexed with `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes = ["nda"]` for the acceptance-test environment (if `summarize-nda` from Phase 6 is not yet indexed). Document the seed approach.</step>
    <step order="2">Author acceptance test in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Phase5/NdaAcceptanceTests.cs`:
      - Upload a synthetic NDA PDF (`tests/integration/Fixtures/nda-synthetic.pdf`)
      - Send chat message "summarize this NDA" with the attachment
      - Assert `DispatchResult.PlaybookId` resolves to the NDA-typed playbook
      - Assert confidence ≥0.7
      - Assert `decidersInvoked` = 0 (single-file path; FR-18).</step>
    <step order="3">Run the test against deployed `bff-dev`. Confirm pass.</step>
    <step order="4">Enumerate FR-15 through FR-21 from spec.md. For each, locate the verification evidence (test result, prior task acceptance):
      FR-15 (DispatchAsync new signature) — task 110
      FR-16 (Phase A ≤50ms total) — task 111 benchmark
      FR-17 (Phase B manifest pre-filter ≤100ms) — task 112
      FR-18 (Phase C decider only on disagreement) — task 113 + 114
      FR-19 (≤2s total budget) — task 118 load test
      FR-20 (slash + NL identical routing) — task 115 + 116
      FR-21 (text-embedding-3-large; no voyage) — verify via grep `voyage` returns zero hits.</step>
    <step order="5">Compile exit-gate report at `notes/handoffs/119-phase5-exit-gate.md` with per-FR pass/fail table + evidence links.</step>
    <step order="6">If ANY FR fails verification, escalate per CLAUDE.md §6 — do NOT mark task ✅.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 119 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 120 (Phase 6 start).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Spec FRs + prior task evidence in notes/handoffs/</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Author acceptance test + stub playbook seed if needed</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet test for acceptance test; integration against bff-dev</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Verify FR-21 (no `voyage` references); verify no leakage in test output</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Exit-gate report at notes/handoffs/</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Phase5/NdaAcceptanceTests.cs</output>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Fixtures/nda-synthetic.pdf</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/119-phase5-exit-gate.md — per-FR pass/fail table</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">NDA acceptance test passes: dispatcher routes "summarize this NDA" + NDA PDF to NDA-typed playbook top-1.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Confidence ≥0.7 on the NDA case.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`decidersInvoked = 0` for single-file path.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All FRs FR-15-21 report PASS with linked evidence.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`grep "voyage" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` returns ZERO hits (FR-21).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Exit-gate report committed.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX updated; current-task.md ready for Phase 6.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Phase 6 task 132 re-runs this acceptance test with the real PB-009 + new specialized playbooks indexed; treat task 119 as the Phase 5 readiness gate, not the final spec.md T-006 sign-off (that lives in Phase 6 + 7 UAT).
  </notes>

